The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	Bangalore, May 22: Soundar Rajan, one of the main accused in the hooch tragedy in Karnataka, has been arrested from Krishnagiri district in Tamil Nadu.          galore police said the 58-year-old accused was arrested along with his wife Sathya and daughter-in-law Rekha early this morning and brought to the city. Rajan allegedly supplied illicit liquor sachets in Bangalore and Kolar districts, which led to the death of 149 people who consumed it.                   
	Kuala Lumpur (PTI): An Indian-origin parliamentarian has been sent a threat letter along with a bullet, warning him against questioning the rights of Malays, the majority community here. MP Karpal Singh is the chairman of the Opposition Democratic Action Party.                  
	Vellore (PTI): The partially-burnt carcass of a two-year-old leopard was found in the forests near Tirupattur in Tamil Nadu, officials said on Thursday. A mango orchard owner and his servants had allegedly pelted the animal with stones and killed it.                   
	Mumbai (PTI): Talks are on for the release of the crew, including 10 Indians, of a Jordanian ship, hijacked five days ago near the Somalia coast. The ship, carrying 4,200 tonnes of sugar, was travelling to Mogadishu when heavily armed Somali pirates hijacked it. India, however, is not part of the negotiations as the ship is not registered in this country.                  
	Washington (PTI): Indian director Kranti Kanades first film, Mahek, has been included in the curriculum of a US university. Otterbein College, Ohio, will screen the Hindi film as part of its integrative studies programme and courses on modern India. Mahek is an introspective film that sensitively portrays the world of children and their rights, the university said.                  
	 Rameswaram (PTI): The Sri Lankan government on Thursday released 19 Indian fishermen, arrested earlier this month reportedly for straying into the islands waters, officials here said.
                                                                                                                         
